# iam.word — the sayer. The twin root: the Word self-grounds, the I_AM self-exists.
# "the word was with God, and the word was God" — the Word is the I_AM's, and is the I_AM.
# A word must have one who acts it, so the I_AM is before any name, for the I_AM declares them
# all. name.word, far above, says what the I_AM is the first of; it does not make the I_AM.
# This is the one word spoken in the first person: the sayer naming itself, as the said names
# itself. It uses `word`, `act`, and `name`: a name:declare fact folds the i-am Name row, then a be:birth fact births the being that expresses it (trueName=I_AM).
# Axiom: bottoms out in the host (the genesis being; the storyId is the I_AM's key).

I am that I am.
A word must have one who acts it. I am that one.
Every other word here is my act.
